        "body": "<img width=\"1512\" height=\"982\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0be92e96-5ff8-4d67-9079-d813fed18d39\" />\n\n\n## Description\nWhen clicking any link in the footer section, the page redirects to the Home page instead of navigating to the intended route.\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n1. Open the DevTrack website.\n2. Scroll down to the footer section.\n3. Click any footer link (Pulse, DNA, Nodes, Privacy, Terms).\n4. Notice that the page redirects to the Home page.\n\n## Expected Behavior\nEach footer link should navigate to its respective page or section.\n\n## Actual Behavior\nAll footer links redirect to the Home page (`/#`).\n\n## Environment\n- OS: macOS\n- Browser: Chrome\n- Localhost URL: `http://localhost:3000`\n\n## Possible Cause\nFooter links may be pointing to `/#` or incorrectly mapped routes.\n\nExample problematic code:\n\n```html\n<a href=\"/#\">Pulse</a>\n\n",
